id conflicts between `JavaConstant.MethodHandle` and `java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle`. I’ll import the necessary constants to simplify testing. I want to verify that the loaded method handle works correctly and produces the expected results using various assertions. Checking the parameter types and method descriptors will help me confirm the method's functionality. It's vital to see if public lookup effectively reveals the method handle as intended.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Understanding MethodHandle RevealDirect**\\n\\nI realize that `Lookup.revealDirect` requires sufficient access to the member, implying that the lookup can \\\"crack\\\" the direct handle. When a handle is created by `publicLookup` for a public method, it should work seamlessly. I also need to consider any issues with the native image related to `MethodHandles.publicLookup` and its use with `findVirtual`. It might be important to check if there's a bug in Byte Buddy 1.8.15 on Java 21 concerning `ClassFileVersion`. However, I don't think it's directly relevant right now.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_uPoY4zxDzSgrmRvAVrtcRxQF|fc_09cc1f4a0d41250a016a2512136d28819681dba5b02f19a1d6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.bytebuddy/byte-buddy/1.8.15/src/test/java/net_bytebuddy/byte_buddy/JavaConstantInnerMethodHandleInnerDispatcherInnerAbstractBaseTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage net_bytebuddy.byte_buddy;\n\nimport net.bytebuddy.utility.JavaConstant;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class JavaConstantInnerMethodHandleInnerDispatcherInnerAbstractBaseTest {\n    @Test\n    void describesLoadedMethodHandleAndLookupType() throws Exception {\n        java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle loadedHandle = MethodHandles.publicLookup().findVirtual(\n                String.class,\n                \"substring\",\n                MethodType.methodType(String.class, int.class, int.class));\n\n        JavaConstant.MethodHandle methodHandle = JavaConstant.MethodHandle.ofLoaded(loadedHandle);\n\n        assertThat(methodHandle.getHandleType()).isEqualTo(JavaConstant.MethodHandle.HandleType.INVOKE_VIRTUAL);\n        assertThat(methodHandle.getOwnerType().represents(String.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(methodHandle.getName()).isEqualTo(\"substring\");\n        assertThat(methodHandle.getReturnType().represents(String.class)).isTrue();\n        assertThat(methodHandle.getDescriptor()).isEqualTo(\"(II)Ljava/lang/String;\");\n        assertThat(JavaConstant.MethodHandle.lookupType(MethodHandles.lookup()))\n                .isEqualTo(JavaConstantInnerMethodHandleInnerDispatcherInnerAbstractBaseTest.class);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1073, "output": 930, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33747, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780814339864, "responseId": "resp_09cc1f4a0d41250a016a2512049f888196a308aed24542d63c"}}
